name: Individual Projects
description: An intensive laboratory or applied research project under the supervision of a Dept. of Psychology faculty member.  Project must be academically demanding and uniquely suitable for the individual student.  Additional information and applications are available at the department and on its website.  This course is open to all Psychology program students.  Not eligible for CR/NCR option.
prerequisites: PSY202H1 (or exclusion), and appropriate background for the proposed work
